== References == {{Reflist|30em}}

{{Infobox person | name = Ahmed Easa | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1985|10|7}} | birth_place = [[Maakurathu (Raa Atoll)|R. Maakurathu]], Maldives | alma_mater = | occupation = Actor | yearsactive = 2011–present | spouse = | children = | works = | awards = }} '''Ahmed Easa''' (born 7 October 1985) is a Maldivian film actor.
==Career== Since his childhood, Ahmed Easa watches [[Bollywood]] films and imitates the acting of [[Sunil Shetty]] in stage performances.<ref name=IntroAanandu>{{cite news |url=https://www.muniavas.com/4049 |title=Aanadu donning a different role in Dhevansoora |language=Divehi|work=Muniavas |last=Rasheed |first=Ahmed |date=27 January 2018 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/AwdMA |deadurl=no |archivedate=6 April 2019 |accessdate=6 April 2019}}</ref> While watching his movies, Easa grew a fondness towards cinema and decided to pursue a career in acting "if granted with a chance worth holding for".<ref name=IntroAanandu/> He was first offered to star in [[Amjad Ibrahim]]'s romantic horror film ''[[Udhabaani]]'' (2009) but he rejected the role since he was "too shy to be in front of the camera with his current physique".<ref name=IntroAanandu/> However, he made his film debut two years later with Hamid Ali's [[Laelaa]] (2011) co-starring [[Yoosuf Shafeeu]], [[Amira Ismail]] and Ali.<ref name=IntroAanandu/><ref name=Laelaa>{{cite news |url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv:80/dhivehi/entertainment/maldives_film_industry/111087 |title="Laela": Why is a good screenplay needed? |language=Divehi|work=Haveeru |last=Nadheem |first=Ahmed |date=6 October 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111011190147/http://www.haveeru.com.mv/dhivehi/entertainment/maldives_film_industry/111087 |deadurl=yes |archivedate=2011-10-11 |accessdate=5 October 2018 |df= }}</ref> The film revolves around two daughters who were forced into arranged marriages by their parent.<ref name=Laelaa/> The film and his performance received negative response from critics; "The newcomer is strictly average in his performance but he needs to be more confident in his moves and work on the dialogue delivery if needs to survive in the industry".<ref name=Laelaa/> The film was declared a flop at box office.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv:80/dhivehi/entertainment/110747 |title=Laela's premiere: A big satisfaction for Hamid |language=Divehi|work=Haveeru |last=Nadheem |first=Ahmed |date=29 September 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111002195434/http://www.haveeru.com.mv/dhivehi/entertainment/110747 |deadurl=yes |archivedate=2011-10-02 |accessdate=11 October 2018 |df= }}</ref>
After shooting a video single with [[Yoosuf Shafeeu]], he proffered Easa to feature in his project ''[[Dhevansoora]]'' (2018), a [[Thriller film|suspense thriller film]] starring Shafeeu, Mariyam Shifa, [[Ali Azim]] and [[Fathimath Azifa]] in pivotal roles.<ref name=mihaaruintro>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/25449 |title="Dhevansoora": A suspense thriller by Eupe |language=Divehi|work=Mihaaru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=21 October 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180328111609/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/25449|deadurl=no |archivedate=28 March 2018 |accessdate=28 March 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/27223 |title="Dhevansoora" to release on February 6 |language=Divehi|work=Mihaaru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=29 November 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180328111057/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/27223|deadurl=no |archivedate=28 March 2018 |accessdate=28 March 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> He initially shot for the role of a policeman, portrayed by Mohamed Faisal in the film, before Shafeeu suggested him to switch for a "more complex" role since he is unable to find anyone "who fits the bill" for that role.<ref name=IntroAanandu/>
