After shooting a video single with [[Yoosuf Shafeeu]], Easa was asked to feature in his thirtieth direction ''[[Dhevansoora]]'' (2018), a [[Thriller film|suspense thriller film]] featuring an [[ensemble cast]] including Shafeeu, Mariyam Shifa, [[Ali Azim]] and [[Fathimath Azifa]] in pivotal roles.<ref name=mihaaruintro>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/25449 |title="Dhevansoora": A suspense thriller by Eupe |language=Divehi|work=Mihaaru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=21 October 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180328111609/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/25449|deadurl=no |archivedate=28 March 2018 |accessdate=28 March 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/27223 |title="Dhevansoora" to release on February 6 |language=Divehi|work=Mihaaru |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=29 November 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180328111057/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/27223|deadurl=no |archivedate=28 March 2018 |accessdate=28 March 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> He initially shot for the role of a policeman, portrayed by [[Mohamed Faisal (actor)|Mohamed Faisal]] in the film, before Shafeeu suggested he switch to a "more complex" role since he was unable to find anyone "who fits the bill" for that role.<ref name=IntroAanandu/> Revolving around a murder investigating, Easa played a delivery boy who has been accused to be involved in the murder crime.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://sun.mv/96653 |title=Dhevansoora is a must watch |language=Divehi |work=Sun |last=Fareeha |first=Aishath |date=4 November 2017 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20181120063343/https://sun.mv/96464 |deadurl=no |archivedate=20 November 2018 |accessdate=20 November 2018 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> The film received positive reviews from critics and was considered a "norm-breaker" for the Maldivian cinema.<ref name=Dhevansoora/> Ahmed Hameed Adam reviewing from VNews applauded Easa's performance while playing the "strong-headed man and the vulnerable attacker".<ref name=Dhevansoora>{{cite news |url=http://vnews.mv/95298 |title=Dhevansoora: Re-writing History of Maldivian Cinema |language=Divehi |work=VNews |last=Adam |first=Ahmed Hameed |date=8 February 2018 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190419092414/http://vnews.mv/95298 |deadurl=no |archivedate=19 April 2019 |accessdate=19 April 2019 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He then starred in the first Maldivian web-series, a romantic drama by [[Fathimath Nahula]], ''[[Huvaa]]''.<ref name=Huvaa>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/31773 |title=Huvaa: Nahula starts her web-series |work=Mihaaru |language=Divehi |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=27 February 2018 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20181130093034/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/31773 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 November 2018 |accessdate=30 November 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The series consisting of sixty episodes and streamed through the digital platform Baiskoafu, centers around a happy and radiant family which breaks into despairing pieces after a tragic incident that led to an unaccountable loss.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sun.mv/110406 |title="Huvaa" is a hard work, it will be nice! |work=Sun |language=Divehi |last=Musthafa |first=Mohamed |date=18 October 2018 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20181130111442/http://sun.mv/110406 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 November 2018 |accessdate=30 November 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/43404 |title="Huvaa" can be viewed through Baiskoafu application |work=Mihaaru |language=Divehi |last=Adhushan |first=Ahmed |date=7 October 2018 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20181130104538/https://mihaaru.com/entertainment/43404 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 November 2018 |accessdate=30 November 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The series and his performance as an irresponsible and lazy husband and a drug addict were positively received.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sun.mv/111524 |title=Nahula's "Huvaa" to be released for streaming tomorrow |work=Sun |language=Divehi |last=Musthafa |first=Mohamed |date=28 November 2018 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20181130112656/http://sun.mv/112249 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 November 2018 |accessdate=30 November 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://sun.mv/112336 |title=First episode of "Huvaa" was a success |work=Sun |language=Divehi |last=Musthafa |first=Mohamed |date=30 November 2018 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20181130113141/http://sun.mv/112336 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 November 2018 |accessdate=30 November 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
